l
==

	>>> import l

If that worked, then we can test for these files:

	>>> py = path('l.py')
	>>> test = path('l.test')

This one might be mising

	>>> tests = path('l.tests')

	>>> l_files = py, test, tests

get_dirs
--------

get_dirs converts a list of strings to a list of paths
	if they exist

	>>> print l.get_dirs(['.', '..', 'No such directory'])
	[path('.'), path('..')]

It defaults to only the current directory

	>>> here = l.get_dirs()
	>>> print here
	[path('.')]

get_files
---------

get_files converts a list of directories to a list of all their files' paths
	(The list of files is flat)

	>>> dirs = l.get_dirs()
	>>> files = l.get_files(dirs)
	>>> #show( files )
	>>> filenames = [ f.name for f in files] 
	>>> #show( l_files )
	>>> [ x in files for x in l_files ]
	[True, True, True]

